The shortest person in recorded history was Chandra Bahadur Dangi, a man from Nepal who stood at just 54.6 centimeters (21.5 inches) tall. Dangi was born in 1939 and worked as a farmer and craftsman before he gained worldwide fame for his small stature. He held the title of the world's shortest living man from 2012 until his death in 2015 at the age of 75.